Male (Fig. 
7A
). Carapace, chelicerae, and pedipalps reddish brown; abdomen and legs yellowish.

Chelicera (Figs 
8C
, 
9B
): Hand with 7 setae, movable finger with 1 submedial seta; fixed finger with 9-11 teeth; movable finger with 10-13 teeth; serrula exterior with 34-38 lamellae; serrula interior with 20-24 lamellae. Galea (Fig. 
9D
) replaced by a small rounded transparent sclerotic knob. Rallum (Fig. 
9C
) with 8 pinnate blade, distal-most blade with expanded base, proximal one short.

Female (paratype) (Fig. 
7B
): Mostly same as holotype.
